<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-538-460  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 538 460.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 8 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Claris updates SmartForm. (SmartForm Designer and SmartFormAssistant programs) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woods, Wendy.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Claris Corp. (product enhancement).andO;Product:   SmartForm Designer (Forms generation software) (productenhancement)Smartform Assistant (Data entry software) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Software packagesSoftware PublishersEnhancementsFunctional Capabilities.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CLARIS UPDATES SMARTFORM SANTA CLARA, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1989 JUL 31 (NB) --The Apple software spin-off Claris Corporation is offering the first updateto SmartForm Designer and SmartForm Assistant since the product'sintroduction earlier this year.andP;  Version 1.1 of the Assistant offers such newfeatures as the ability to gorup form sets into a file.andP;  Users can thenperform database- like searches within a form set, such as &quot;find all formscompleted between January 1 and January 31.&quot; Users can also export entireform sets to SYLK, DIF, DBF and WKS formats in order to use them in programssuch as FileMaker, Excel, Lotus 1-2-3, or dBASE.andP;  The new version ofSmartform Designer, 1.1, $399, allows users to designate entry fields in anelectronic form to be filled with pictures, instead of words or numbers.andO;There is also more flexibility in drawing effects, based on support ofEncapsulated Postscript (EPS).andP;  Claris says its products are in use at BlueCross and Blue Shield in Washington, D.C., where some 3,000 forms have beencreated and updated using SmartForm Designer.andP;  8,000 forms have been createdby 3M Company's in-house forms management department, according to Claris.andO;(Wendy Woods/19890731)</TEXT></DOC>